{{#if user}}
    {{> user-menu }}
{{else}}
    {{> welcome-menu }}
{{/if}}
<div class="container">
    <div class="row mt-3">
        <div class="col-sm-8">
            <h1 class="mt-3 fs-1 special-font">
                #About <span style="color: #007139;">Easy</span><span style="color: #f0ab00;">Bites</span>
            </h1>
            <p>
                We are EasyBites, a website that specialises in creating low-cost recipes for students that can be 
                made with the ingredients you already have in your fridge. Our goal is to help you save money, save time 
                and enjoy delicious meals at the same time.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-3">
            <img src="/images/im_about_1.png" alt="Image About 1" class="img-fluid">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row mt-3">
        <div class="col-sm-3">
            <img src="/images/im_about_2.png" alt="Image About 2" class="img-fluid">
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-8">
            <h1 class="mt-3 fs-1 special-font">#Our values and personality</h1>
            <p>
                At EasyBites, we value sustainability and avoiding food waste. We believe in flexibility in cooking 
                and want to show you how to find creative solutions to cook with the ingredients available and not neglect 
                the taste.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row mt-3">
        <div class="col-sm-9">
            <h1 class="mt-3 fs-1 special-font">#Our goals</h1>
            <ul>
                <li>Cook on the cheap: Discover recipes that won't break your student budget but are still delicious.</li>
                <li>Save time: Our simple and easy recipes allow you to prepare delicious meals quickly and efficiently.</li>
                <li>Learn new recipes that are easy: Expand your cooking repertoire and try new and easy recipes that are suitable for beginners.</li>
                <li>No food waste: Use the ingredients you already have to create delicious dishes while reducing food waste.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-2">
            <img src="/images/im_about_3.png" alt="Image About 3" class="img-fluid">
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
